## 1. mbuzz — Best for Validated Attribution

**Why consider mbuzz:** Northbeam's ML is sophisticated, but how do you know it's accurate? mbuzz proves attribution with incrementality testing.

### What mbuzz Offers

**Transparent attribution you can actually understand.** No black-box ML—just clear models with logic you can inspect and customize. 8 built-in models including Markov Chain and Shapley Value, plus a DSL for custom rules.

**Server-side tracking that captures 95%+ of events.** Northbeam still relies on client-side pixels that ad blockers defeat. mbuzz tracks on your backend—no missing data.

**Side-by-side model comparison.** See how First Touch, Last Touch, Linear, Time Decay, U-Shaped, and data-driven models credit the same conversions differently. Northbeam gives you one number; mbuzz shows you the range.

**LTV attribution, not just first purchase.** Your worst first-month channel might be your best LTV channel. mbuzz tracks recurring revenue back to original acquisition source—see which campaigns drive customers who stick around.

**Pricing without traffic penalties:**

| Tier | Records/Month | Price |
|------|-------------|-------|
| Free | Up to 50K | $0 |
| Starter | Up to 1M | $29/mo |
| Growth | Up to 5M | $99/mo |
| Pro | Up to 25M | $299/mo |

Compare to Northbeam's pageview-based pricing that can hit $2-5K/month for high-traffic sites.

**10-minute setup** with native SDKs for Rails, Django, Laravel, and Node.js. Export everything anytime—your data, no lock-in.

### mbuzz vs Northbeam

| Factor | Northbeam | mbuzz |
|--------|-----------|-------|
| Attribution method | ML fractional credit | MTA + Incrementality |
| Validation | Trust the algorithm | Experimental proof |
| Transparency | Black box | Open methodology |
| Learning curve | Steep | Moderate |
| Target size | $40M+ brands | Flexible |

### The Validation Difference

```
Northbeam Approach:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
├── ML assigns fractional credit
├── Total sums to 100% (no over-attribution)
├── But is the allocation actually correct?
└── No way to verify without external testing

mbuzz Approach:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
├── MTA assigns credit
├── Incrementality test validates
│   └── "Does turning off Meta actually reduce revenue by 30%?"
├── Calibrate MTA with ground truth
└── Confidence in attribution accuracy
```

### Best For

- Teams who want proof, not just models
- Brands skeptical of black-box attribution
- Those willing to run experiments
- Companies scaling beyond Northbeam's value

